---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const investmentRows = [
	{ service: 'Psychological Evaluations', rate: '$1,500', note: 'ADHD, autism, diagnostic clarification, learning disorders, personality' },
	{ service: 'Psychoeducational Evaluations', rate: '$1,500', note: 'Dyslexia, learning disorders, giftedness, 2E, academic achievement' },
	{ service: 'Clinician Consultation', rate: 'By inquiry', note: 'Billing, credentialing, practice operations' },
	{ service: 'CEU Trainings', rate: 'By inquiry', note: 'ADHD assessment, autism evaluation, custom topics' },
];

const paymentMethods = [
	'Credit and debit cards',
	'HSA and FSA cards accepted',
	'Zelle',
	'Venmo',
];
---

<Layout
	title="Investment | Morning Tide Consulting and Collective"
	description="Transparent pricing for psychological and psychoeducational evaluations, clinician consultations, and continuing education trainings. Self-pay only — out-of-network with health insurance."
>
	<main class="px-6 py-16 lg:px-10 lg:py-20">
		<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-8">
			<p class="eyebrow">Investment</p>
			<h1 class="max-w-4xl text-5xl leading-none text-(--color-ink) sm:text-6xl">Transparent pricing. Out-of-network. No surprises.</h1>
			<p class="max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
				Morning Tide operates as a private-pay practice. This model protects your privacy, eliminates insurance-driven limitations on evaluation scope, and allows reports to be completed within one week rather than months.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-6xl rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
			<p class="eyebrow">Service Investment</p>
			<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
				{investmentRows.map((row) => (
					<div class="premium-card rounded-3xl p-5 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr] sm:items-center sm:gap-4">
						<p class="text-base font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">{row.service}</p>
						<p class="text-base font-semibold text-(--color-accent)">{row.rate}</p>
						<p class="text-sm text-(--color-muted)">{row.note}</p>
					</div>
				))}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 grid max-w-6xl gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="section-shell rounded-4xl p-8">
				<p class="eyebrow">Why Private-Pay</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">Better evaluations, faster results, complete privacy.</h2>
				<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>No insurance company dictating what gets tested or how the report reads</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>Sensitive diagnostic information stays out of insurance databases</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>Reports are completed within one week — not months</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>HSA and FSA cards are accepted, making evaluations reimbursable through pre-tax funds</span></li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
				<p class="eyebrow">Payment Methods</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">Flexible payment options.</h2>
				<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">
					{paymentMethods.map((method) => (
						<li class="flex gap-3">
							<span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span>
							<span>{method}</span>
						</li>
					))}
				</ul>
				<div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-section-tint) p-5">
					<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">Payment Plans</p>
					<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-(--color-muted)">Payment plans may be available on a case-by-case basis. Contact us to discuss options before your evaluation.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-6xl rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
			<div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">Superbills</p>
					<p class="mt-4 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">A superbill with CPT codes and diagnostic information is provided after each evaluation. Many clients submit these to their insurance for partial out-of-network reimbursement.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">What Is Included</p>
					<p class="mt-4 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">Each evaluation includes a clinical intake, comprehensive testing session, a detailed written report, and a feedback session to review findings and recommendations.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">Questions</p>
					<a class="mt-4 inline-flex rounded-full bg-(--color-accent) px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-(--shadow-brand)" href="/#contact">Ask about pricing</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 grid max-w-6xl gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="section-shell rounded-4xl p-8">
				<p class="eyebrow">Insurance Benefit Verification</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">We can check your out-of-network benefits.</h2>
				<p class="mt-5 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
					Although MCC is out-of-network with health insurance, many plans offer out-of-network benefits that can reimburse a portion of evaluation costs. We are able to verify your insurance benefits and check your out-of-network coverage before your evaluation begins — so you know what to expect.
				</p>
				<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>We verify out-of-network benefits on your behalf prior to your evaluation</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>Superbills with CPT codes are provided after every evaluation for reimbursement submission</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span>HSA and FSA cards are accepted as payment at the time of service</span></li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
				<p class="eyebrow">Medical Necessity</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">Not all evaluations are covered by health insurance.</h2>
				<p class="mt-5 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
					Health insurance plans generally only cover services that meet the criteria for <strong>medical necessity</strong> — meaning the evaluation must be required to diagnose or treat a medical or mental health condition. Many evaluations fall outside this scope:
				</p>
				<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span><strong>Educational purposes</strong> — testing for school accommodations, IEP/504 plans, or giftedness identification is considered educational, not medical</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span><strong>Legal or forensic purposes</strong> — evaluations for custody proceedings, disability claims, or court-ordered assessments are not viewed as medically necessary by insurers</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span><strong>Workplace or vocational evaluations</strong> — testing requested for employment accommodations or career planning typically falls outside medical coverage</span></li>
					<li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span><span><strong>Comprehensive or elective testing</strong> — insurers may limit testing to a narrow set of measures and deny broader evaluations that go beyond the minimum diagnostic threshold</span></li>
				</ul>
				<p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">Private-pay removes these restrictions entirely, allowing the evaluation scope to be driven by the clinical question — not by what an insurer will authorize.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-6xl rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
			<div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.25fr]">
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">Good Faith Estimate</p>
					<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">Your right to a cost estimate.</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
					<p>Under the <strong>No Surprises Act</strong>, health care providers are required to give patients who are uninsured or self-pay a <strong>Good Faith Estimate</strong> of expected charges before services are provided.</p>
					<p>You have the right to receive a Good Faith Estimate for the total expected cost of any non-emergency health care services, including psychological and psychoeducational evaluations. MCC provides this estimate in advance of every scheduled evaluation.</p>
					<p>If you receive a bill that is at least $400 more than your Good Faith Estimate, you may dispute the bill. For questions or more information about your right to a Good Faith Estimate, visit <a class="font-semibold text-(--color-accent) underline underline-offset-4" href="https://www.cms.gov/nosurprises" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">cms.gov/nosurprises</a>.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
